NEXUS COMMAND: VANGUARD PROTOCOL 2026
MASTER ARCHITECTURE, DEFENSE, & EXECUTION RULES
1. PROJECT SOURCE OF TRUTH & COST OPTIMIZATION (CRITICAL)
Absolute Roadmap Enforcement: Always reference MASTER_BUILD_ROADMAP.md for feature planning.

Pre-Indexed Context: To minimize massive cache-read costs, read the .stack-shared-ai/ directory index to understand routes and models before exploring raw source files.

Anti-Monolith Sprints: Do not attempt 500-line refactors in a single prompt. Break large changes into focused 100-line sessions to prevent context degradation and token waste.

Strategic Model Switching: Use premium models (Claude 3.5 Sonnet/Opus) exclusively in Plan Mode for complex reasoning, then execute the agreed-upon plan using the cheaper Composer-1 (Auto mode).

2. DATABASE DEFENSE & ANTI-DELETION PROTOCOL
Zero Data Loss Mandate: You are explicitly forbidden from writing destructive Firestore migrations or dropping unmapped keys.

Lazy Migration (Read-Repair): If required keys (sportId, schemaVersion, tenantId) are missing on read, patch the object with safe defaults in memory and execute an asynchronous non-blocking merge write ({ merge: true }).

Strict Tenant Isolation: Every database read/write must explicitly enforce clubId or tenantId to prevent cross-tenant exposure.

3. PROJECT IDENTITY & TECHNO-FUTURIST AESTHETIC
Platform Identity: "Nexus Command" — a professional-grade, gamified SaaS platform for youth athlete development.

The UI Aesthetic: "Techno-Futurist SIEM / Cyberpunk." It must feel like an ultra-premium cybersecurity Mission Control dashboard. No flat, boring white backgrounds.  

Colors: Deep dark mode (bg-[#020202]), neon cyan/indigo accents (text-[#00f0ff], border-[#00f0ff]), and stark whites.

Textures & Layouts: True Glassmorphism with deep backdrop-blur. Implement rigid Bento Grid layouts using CSS clamp() functions to build fluid, scannable hierarchies without static media queries.  

Micro-Typography: Interface text must be ultra-small (tw-text-[10px]), use monospace fonts, and employ aggressive letter spacing (tw-tracking-widest).

4. TECH STACK & STRICT SVELTE 5 MANDATES
Core Stack: Svelte 5 (Strict Runes), SvelteKit, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Firebase v2 Modular SDK.

Reactivity: Use Svelte 5 Runes strictly ($state, $derived, $effect). You must use untrack() for goto() calls inside $effect blocks to prevent infinite execution loops.

Tailwind Prefix: You MUST use the tw- prefix for all utility classes.

5. THE VANGUARD TRINITY PATTERN (UI ARCHITECTURE)
The Shell (+page.svelte): The mounting layer. Handles fixed layout containers.

The Brain ([Name]Engine.svelte.ts): The pure TypeScript Svelte 5 state machine.

The Glass ([Name]Arena.svelte): The pure presentation layer.

The HUD ([Name]HUD.svelte): The HTML/Tailwind control overlay. The root container must be tw-pointer-events-none so it does not block interactions with the board underneath.

6. CODE EXECUTION DIRECTIVES
Do Not Append Solutions: When instructed to refactor, rewrite the necessary logic cleanly. Never append alternative code blocks to the bottom of the file.

Search and Destroy Redundancy: When replacing a legacy module, explicitly delete the deprecated HTML forms and permanently delete orphaned .svelte files.